.TH "ring_buffer_nr_pages" 9 "ring_buffer_nr_pages" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ring_buffer_nr_pages \- get the number of buffer pages in the ring buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" ring_buffer_nr_pages
.BI "(struct trace_buffer *buffer "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
The ring_buffer to get the number of pages from
.IP "cpu" 12
The cpu of the ring_buffer to get the number of pages from
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of pages used by a per_cpu buffer of the ring buffer.
